        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 5:39PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 539 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Raeford, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Raeford, Fort Bragg, Antioch, Hope Mills, Silver City,
Cedar Creek, Bushy Lake Natural Area, Rockfish, and Bowmore.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
